title: A NASA astronaut will finally spend a full year in space
summary: "I'm really excited to see how my body does when I return."

title: SpaceX waiting for FAA to approve launch licence for Starship’s second flight
summary: With the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) having closed the mishap investigation into the anomaly during the first Integrated Flight Test of Starship, SpaceX is waiting for its launch license for the second test flight of the world’s most powerful rocket.

title: ULA has ‘no issues’ with Space Force plan to select three national security launch providers
summary: United Launch Alliance, one of just two U.S. companies that provide national security launch services, does not have a problem with DoD’s decision to add a third competitor, a senior ULA executive said Sept. 13.

title: BREAKING! NASA Releases Artemis 1 In Flight Anomalies Breakdown
summary: NASA has released the full list of In Flight Anomalies (IFAs) from the Artemis 1 mission to TLP Network via a Freedom Of Information Act (FOIA) request.

title: SpaceX says it is no longer losing money with Starlink production
summary: SpaceX Vice President of Starlink, Jonathan Hofeller, said today that the company is no longer taking a hit financially for producing Starlink...
